Here's the command, run from the repo root:
  
  cd /Users/techno/SynologyDrive/coding/repositories/LeadPilot
  uvicorn leadpilot.app:app --app-dir src --port 8000

  That runs it in the foreground in your terminal (Ctrl+C stops it — handy for watching the logs directly).

  Two variations worth knowing:

  If the old process is wedged (port already in use), kill it first:
  pkill -f "uvicorn leadpilot.app"; sleep 1
  uvicorn leadpilot.app:app --app-dir src --port 8000

  With auto-reload (picks up code/template changes without restarting — good while we're iterating):
  uvicorn leadpilot.app:app --app-dir src --port 8000 --reload

  Prerequisites if it's a fresh boot: the venv must be active (source .venv/bin/activate — or however you normally activate it)
  and the dev database running (scripts/devdb.sh start). Port 8000 specifically matters — the Google Picker API key is
  referrer-locked to localhost:8000.

  You can also run it from inside this session anytime by typing ! pkill -f uvicorn; uvicorn leadpilot.app:app --app-dir src 
  --port 8000 — or just ask me to restart it.

http://localhost:8000 to reach app — must be localhost, not 127.0.0.1:
both the Google OAuth redirect URI and the Picker API key's referrer
restriction are locked to localhost:8000, and browsers treat
127.0.0.1 as a different origin for cookies. Logging in on one and
hitting the Google OAuth callback on the other loses your session
mid-flow ("Not authenticated").


