Yes, database first. The good news: devdb.sh start is safe to run even when the DB is already up (it just prints "Already running." and
  exits cleanly), so you can chain the two into one command and use it every time:

  scripts/devdb.sh start && .venv/bin/uvicorn leadpilot.app:app --reload --app-dir src

  Run it from the repo root. I used .venv/bin/uvicorn directly so it works whether or not you've activated the virtualenv — if you prefer
  activating first, this is equivalent:

# create a virtual environment
  python -m venv .venv

  # activate it
  source .venv/bin/activate
  scripts/devdb.sh start && uvicorn leadpilot.app:app --reload --app-dir src

  One note on ordering: strictly speaking uvicorn will start fine without the DB (connections are made per-request, which is why you got a
  500 page rather than a startup crash), so the && isn't load-bearing — but starting the DB first means the first page you load actually
  works. When you're done, the DB keeps running in the background; scripts/devdb.sh stop shuts it down, or just leave it — it survives
  until reboot/sleep, which is why it was down tonight.
